Text:
Alexia watches Delta's massacre in silent awe from
a safe distance.
Hey...is that really one of Shadow's friends?
Ah!
Oh? What do you mean?
The way they fight is completely different.

The Shadow I know is a masterful swordsman. But that
right there is just violence without any finesse.

Delta's display is far from what Alexia considers to
be strength.

I mean, I can see that she's powerful, but is that
really the best way to use it?
Perhaps she's just a special kind of meathead...

The army of Nelsons is obliterated in the blink of
an eye.
And with that, the world comes apart.

How... Over 100 clones, slain like they were
nothing...!
You were a researcher once, weren't you?
Ah!

No matter how many copies you create, you only have
one mind—not nearly enough to control all of those
extra bodies.

Your hundred clones may as well have been a hundred
scarecrows.
Alpha approaches with her blade in one hand.
Eep...!
Nelson backs away from her.

It would also seem that there is a limit to how many
clones you can make.
Alpha states the observation matter-of-factly.

And it is the truth—Nelson no longer has the strength
to produce any more clones.
That's why...
Yes! Olivier!
Olivierrrr!
Come!
Come forth!
Obey me!
Olivierrrrrr!!!

A tear in space opens in response to Nelson's
pitiful cries.

From it emerges a lone woman...one who bears a
striking resemblance to Alpha…
The great hero, Olivier...

Yes, it is indeed the hero. But there is no life in
her eyes.They are empty like two glass orbs...yet
they hold a certain sadness.
Olivier... So it's true...
Grrr...
Lady Alpha!
We've finished our investigation!
We can make an exit whenever you're ready!
Good.
Then let us be on our way.
Alpha turns around to leave.
W-Wait...! You're leaving? You mean to...escape?!
I-I cannot believe it...

We have no interest in weaklings and unreliable
memories. Our purpose here today was merely
to sever the source of your power.

And we've also learned more about the Sanctuary's
defenses.

We'll be back to pay you another visit...at our
leisure.

Y-You think I'll simply let you w-waltz out of
here...?!
Oh, do you intend to pursue us?
Ack!
Nelson hides behind Olivier.
Delta, we're leaving.
Grrr...
*sigh*
Delta.
Yes, ma'am! I'm sorry!

Delta follows after Alpha with her ears down and her
tail tucked meekly.
You all may come as well.
I'm going with them.
But maybe you should stay, Alexia?
Dismal places like this suit you well, after all.

Oh yeah?! And what you makes you think I belong in
this bald buffoon's hideaway?
*sigh*

Everyone enters the glowing light, and peace
returns to the Sanctuary.
Nelson heaves a sigh of relief.

B-But no matter, I won't soon forget that Alpha.
With her blood, I can bring the Tears one step
closer to perfection.

As for how I'm going to explain all of this to the
other factions... Ah yes, I shall say I lured our
foes here, sprung my trap, and unmasked them.
Why, I daresay I may even be recognized for my—
Hm?
A rat creeping about in the centrum...?
Hmph, crushing them will make for a fine divers—
What?!
O-Olivier, come with me!

Why, oh why do these things always have to happen on
my watch...
